Nap 1.Standard duration of nap//同步完成
2.When is the best time for nap? Reference Lack of sleep at night or sleep quality is not good. Appropriate nap in the day can replenish energy. Generally speaking, a 15-30 minute nap before 1PM will refresh you and improve your alertness and productivity in the afternoon. However, the nap in the day should not be over 45 minutes. Otherwise you may enter into deep sleep, and your body temperature will drop, which will make you feel very sleepy, or dizzy and other adverse symptoms. Also, if you enter into deep sleep in the day, you will feel less sleepy at night, which will make it difficult for you to fall asleep in the night. The most important part of the body clock is the body temperature rhythm. When the body temperature rises, people will feel more awake. When your body temperature drops, you feel tired and sleepy. Body temperature fluctuates periodically throughout the day. It starts to rise in the morning, then drops at noon and continues to rise until night. Therefore, the best time to nap is when your body temperature falls back at noon (usually before 1 a.m.). The late daytime nap time will disturb the body temperature rhythm and affect the sleep quality at night. * single sleep of less than 3 hours was counted as sporadic naps. [1] The circadian rhythm of body temperature.Frontiers in Bioscience, 2010(15): 564-594. \n[2] <<Diagnosis and treatment manual of sleep disorders>> people\'s health publishing house, September 2012, 1st edition Sedentary reminder Sedentary reminder
